# Backend Python Practices

- Use explicit typing and keep `mypy` clean for new backend code.
- Place API routes under `backend/app/api/` and shared config in `backend/app/core/`.
- Keep service/domain logic in `backend/app/services/`; route handlers stay thin.
- Validate request/response boundaries with typed models where appropriate.
- Add or update tests in `backend/tests/` for changed behavior.
- Keep imports sorted and formatting compliant with `ruff` and `black`.
